40|$|Abstract- This paper adopts {{ordinary}} CCD {{cameras and}} <b>IR</b> <b>filters</b> to constitute <b>IR</b> cameras for a marker-based quadri-ocular tracking system. However, the <b>IR</b> <b>filters</b> {{will affect the}} accuracy of the tracking system. Therefore, this paper analyses the refraction of <b>IR</b> <b>filters</b> and finds <b>IR</b> <b>filters</b> will bring about the biggish radial distortion on imaging process. And then, this paper directly uses Zhang’s technique to calibrate the parameters of IR cameras in infrared environment by adjusting the imaging conditions of calibration. To improve the accuracy and satisfy the real-time requirement of the tracking system, a real-time method to correct the radial distortion is proposed in this paper. The experiment...|$|R
